37 // Pass debugging information. Often it is useful to find out what pass is ----
38 // running when a crash occurs in a utility. When this library is compiled with ----
39 // debugging on, a command line option (--debug-pass) is enabled that causes the ----
40 // pass name to be printed before it executes. ----
41 // ----
42 ----
43 namespace { ----
44 // Different debug levels that can be enabled... ----
45 enum PassDebugLevel { ----
46 Disabled, Arguments, Structure, Executions, Details ----
47 }; ----
48 } // namespace ----
49 ----
50 static cl::opt PassDebugging( ----
51 "debug-pass", cl::Hidden, ----
52 cl::desc("Print legacy PassManager debugging information"), ----
53 cl::values(clEnumVal(Disabled, "disable debug output"), ----
54 clEnumVal(Arguments, "print pass arguments to pass to 'opt'"), ----
55 clEnumVal(Structure, "print pass structure before run()"), ----
56 clEnumVal(Executions, "print pass name before it is executed"), ----
57 clEnumVal(Details, "print pass details when it is executed"))); ----
58 ----
59 /// isPassDebuggingExecutionsOrMore - Return true if -debug-pass=Executions ----
60 /// or higher is specified. ----
61 bool PMDataManager::isPassDebuggingExecutionsOrMore() const { 0
62 return PassDebugging >= Executions; 0
63 } ----

65 unsigned PMDataManager::initSizeRemarkInfo( 0
66 Module &M, StringMap> &FunctionToInstrCount) { ----
67 // Only calculate getInstructionCount if the size-info remark is requested. ----
68 unsigned InstrCount = 0; 0
69 ----
70 // Collect instruction counts for every function. We'll use this to emit ----
71 // per-function size remarks later. ----
72 for (Function &F : M) { 0
73 unsigned FCount = F.getInstructionCount(); 0
74 ----
75 // Insert a record into FunctionToInstrCount keeping track of the current ----
76 // size of the function as the first member of a pair. Set the second ----
77 // member to 0; if the function is deleted by the pass, then when we get ----
78 // here, we'll be able to let the user know that F no longer contributes to ----
79 // the module. ----
80 FunctionToInstrCount[F.getName().str()] = 0
81 std::pair(FCount, 0); 0
82 InstrCount += FCount; 0
83 } ----
84 return InstrCount; 0
85 } ----
86 ----
87 void PMDataManager::emitInstrCountChangedRemark( 0
88 Pass *P, Module &M, int64_t Delta, unsigned CountBefore, ----
89 StringMap> &FunctionToInstrCount, ----
90 Function *F) { ----
91 // If it's a pass manager, don't emit a remark. (This hinges on the assumption ----
92 // that the only passes that return non-null with getAsPMDataManager are pass ----
93 // managers.) The reason we have to do this is to avoid emitting remarks for ----
94 // CGSCC passes. ----
95 if (P->getAsPMDataManager()) 0
96 return; 0
97 ----
98 // Set to true if this isn't a module pass or CGSCC pass. ----
99 bool CouldOnlyImpactOneFunction = (F != nullptr); 0
100 ----
101 // Helper lambda that updates the changes to the size of some function. ----
102 auto UpdateFunctionChanges = ----
103 [&FunctionToInstrCount](Function &MaybeChangedFn) { 0
104 // Update the total module count. ----
105 unsigned FnSize = MaybeChangedFn.getInstructionCount(); 0
106 auto It = FunctionToInstrCount.find(MaybeChangedFn.getName()); 0
107 ----
108 // If we created a new function, then we need to add it to the map and ----
109 // say that it changed from 0 instructions to FnSize. ----
110 if (It == FunctionToInstrCount.end()) { 0
111 FunctionToInstrCount[MaybeChangedFn.getName()] = 0
112 std::pair(0, FnSize); 0
113 return; 0
114 } ----
115 // Insert the new function size into the second member of the pair. This ----
116 // tells us whether or not this function changed in size. ----
117 It->second.second = FnSize; 0
118 }; 0
119 ----
120 // We need to initially update all of the function sizes. ----
121 // If no function was passed in, then we're either a module pass or an ----
122 // CGSCC pass. ----
123 if (!CouldOnlyImpactOneFunction) 0
124 std::for_each(M.begin(), M.end(), UpdateFunctionChanges); 0
125 else ----
126 UpdateFunctionChanges(*F); 0
127 ----
128 // Do we have a function we can use to emit a remark? ----
129 if (!CouldOnlyImpactOneFunction) { 0
130 // We need a function containing at least one basic block in order to output ----
131 // remarks. Since it's possible that the first function in the module ----
132 // doesn't actually contain a basic block, we have to go and find one that's ----
133 // suitable for emitting remarks. ----
134 auto It = llvm::find_if(M, [](const Function &Fn) { return !Fn.empty(); }); 0
135 ----
136 // Didn't find a function. Quit. ----
137 if (It == M.end()) 0
138 return; 0
139 ----
140 // We found a function containing at least one basic block. ----
141 F = &*It; 0
142 } ----
143 int64_t CountAfter = static_cast(CountBefore) + Delta; 0
144 BasicBlock &BB = *F->begin(); 0
145 OptimizationRemarkAnalysis R("size-info", "IRSizeChange", ----
146 DiagnosticLocation(), &BB); 0
147 // FIXME: Move ore namespace to DiagnosticInfo so that we can use it. This ----
148 // would let us use NV instead of DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument. ----
149 R << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("Pass", P->getPassName()) 0
150 << ": IR instruction count changed from " 0
151 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("IRInstrsBefore", CountBefore) 0
152 << " to " 0
153 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("IRInstrsAfter", CountAfter) 0
154 << "; Delta: " 0
155 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("DeltaInstrCount", Delta); 0
156 F->getContext().diagnose(R); // Not using ORE for layering reasons. 0
157 ----
158 // Emit per-function size change remarks separately. ----
159 std::string PassName = P->getPassName().str(); 0
160 ----
161 // Helper lambda that emits a remark when the size of a function has changed. ----
162 auto EmitFunctionSizeChangedRemark = [&FunctionToInstrCount, &F, &BB, 0
163 &PassName](StringRef Fname) { 0
164 unsigned FnCountBefore, FnCountAfter; ----
165 std::pair &Change = FunctionToInstrCount[Fname]; 0
166 std::tie(FnCountBefore, FnCountAfter) = Change; 0
167 int64_t FnDelta = static_cast(FnCountAfter) - 0
168 static_cast(FnCountBefore); 0
169 ----
170 if (FnDelta == 0) 0
171 return; 0
172 ----
173 // FIXME: We shouldn't use BB for the location here. Unfortunately, because ----
174 // the function that we're looking at could have been deleted, we can't use ----
175 // it for the source location. We *want* remarks when a function is deleted ----
176 // though, so we're kind of stuck here as is. (This remark, along with the ----
177 // whole-module size change remarks really ought not to have source ----
178 // locations at all.) ----
179 OptimizationRemarkAnalysis FR("size-info", "FunctionIRSizeChange", ----
180 DiagnosticLocation(), &BB); 0
181 FR << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("Pass", PassName) 0
182 << ": Function: " 0
183 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("Function", Fname) 0
184 << ": IR instruction count changed from " 0
185 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("IRInstrsBefore", 0
186 FnCountBefore) 0
187 << " to " 0
188 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("IRInstrsAfter", 0
189 FnCountAfter) 0
190 << "; Delta: " 0
191 << DiagnosticInfoOptimizationBase::Argument("DeltaInstrCount", FnDelta); 0
192 F->getContext().diagnose(FR); 0
193 ----
194 // Update the function size. ----
195 Change.first = FnCountAfter; 0
196 }; 0
197 ----
198 // Are we looking at more than one function? If so, emit remarks for all of ----
199 // the functions in the module. Otherwise, only emit one remark. ----
200 if (!CouldOnlyImpactOneFunction) 0
201 std::for_each(FunctionToInstrCount.keys().begin(), 0
202 FunctionToInstrCount.keys().end(), 0
203 EmitFunctionSizeChangedRemark); ----
204 else ----
205 EmitFunctionSizeChangedRemark(F->getName().str()); 0
206 } 0

208 void PassManagerPrettyStackEntry::print(raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
209 if (!V && !M) 0
210 OS << "Releasing pass '"; 0
211 else ----
212 OS << "Running pass '"; 0
213 ----
214 OS << P->getPassName() << "'"; 0
215 ----
216 if (M) { 0
217 OS << " on module '" << M->getModuleIdentifier() << "'.\n"; 0
218 return; 0
219 } ----
220 if (!V) { 0
221 OS << '\n'; 0
222 return; 0
223 } ----
224 ----
225 OS << " on "; 0
226 if (isa(V)) 0
227 OS << "function"; 0
228 else if (isa(V)) 0
229 OS << "basic block"; 0
230 else ----
231 OS << "value"; 0
232 ----
233 OS << " '"; 0
234 V->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/false, M); 0
235 OS << "'\n"; 0
236 } ----

350 } ----
351 } ----
352 wasRun = false; 0
353 } ----

356 // Return true if any function is modified by a pass. ----

1600 /// Add RequiredPass into list of lower level passes required by pass P. ----
1601 /// RequiredPass is run on the fly by Pass Manager when P requests it ----
1602 /// through getAnalysis interface. ----
1603 void MPPassManager::addLowerLevelRequiredPass(Pass *P, Pass *RequiredPass) { 0
1604 assert(RequiredPass && "No required pass?"); 0
1605 assert(P->getPotentialPassManagerType() == PMT_ModulePassManager && 0
1606 "Unable to handle Pass that requires lower level Analysis pass"); ----
1607 assert((P->getPotentialPassManagerType() < 0
1608 RequiredPass->getPotentialPassManagerType()) && ----
1609 "Unable to handle Pass that requires lower level Analysis pass"); ----
1610 ----
1611 legacy::FunctionPassManagerImpl *FPP = OnTheFlyManagers[P]; 0
1612 if (!FPP) { 0
1613 FPP = new legacy::FunctionPassManagerImpl(); 0
1614 // FPP is the top level manager. ----
1615 FPP->setTopLevelManager(FPP); 0
1616 ----
1617 OnTheFlyManagers[P] = FPP; 0
1618 } ----
1619 const PassInfo *RequiredPassPI = ----
1620 TPM->findAnalysisPassInfo(RequiredPass->getPassID()); 0
1621 ----
1622 Pass *FoundPass = nullptr; 0
1623 if (RequiredPassPI && RequiredPassPI->isAnalysis()) { 0
1624 FoundPass = ----
1625 ((PMTopLevelManager*)FPP)->findAnalysisPass(RequiredPass->getPassID()); 0
1626 } ----
1627 if (!FoundPass) { 0

1629 // This should be guaranteed to add RequiredPass to the passmanager given ----
1630 // that we checked for an available analysis above. ----
1631 FPP->add(RequiredPass); 0
1632 } ----
1633 // Register P as the last user of FoundPass or RequiredPass. ----
1634 SmallVector LU; 0
1635 LU.push_back(FoundPass); 0
1636 FPP->setLastUser(LU, P); 0
1637 } 0
